247
00:14:50,869 --> 00:14:53,870
Yes! When I went into the cash register room

248
00:14:53,870 --> 00:14:55,670
because I wanted to check on the accident that happened

249
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:57,970
in the snowy mountain on December 28th,

250
00:14:57,970 --> 00:15:00,370
and asked you to lend me the computer,

251
00:15:00,370 --> 00:15:03,470
you weren't surprised, were you?

252
00:15:03,470 --> 00:15:05,270
That's how I figured out

253
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:06,885
you were the one who wanted this case checked

254
00:15:06,885 --> 00:15:10,670
and were somehow involved with the accident in the mountain.

255
00:15:10,670 --> 00:15:12,470
In the picture with Mr. Maruoka who died in the mountain,

256
00:15:12,470 --> 00:15:14,893
his daughter was in it too.

257
00:15:14,893 --> 00:15:17,870
And, you were wearing a wedding ring,

258
00:15:17,870 --> 00:15:21,670
so I thought maybe you got married and your last name changed!

259
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:22,901
Really...

260
00:15:22,901 --> 00:15:25,270
You're really something, aren't you, Conan?

261
00:15:25,270 --> 00:15:27,370
Of... Of course.

262
00:15:27,370 --> 00:15:32,470
I did all of what I did because Pops told me to do it.

263
00:15:32,470 --> 00:15:35,870
Just as would be expected of the Sleeping Kogoro!

264
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:39,870
But, the sender of this mail is quite a great detective himself!

265
00:15:39,870 --> 00:15:43,570
Everything aside from your identity hit the bull's eye.

266
00:15:43,570 --> 00:15:44,570
I wonder who it is?

267
00:15:44,570 --> 00:15:46,925
Maybe that person is still here on this floor.

268
00:15:46,925 --> 00:15:49,470
Then, maybe if you send a thank you mail,

269
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:50,929
that person will appear?

270
00:15:50,929 --> 00:15:52,370
No, way.

271
00:15:52,370 --> 00:15:53,570
From what's written there,

272
00:15:53,570 --> 00:15:56,570
it seems that the person doesn't want to get involved.

273
00:16:01,770 --> 00:16:02,941
What?

274
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:04,670
Maybe it's him?

275
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:07,870
I'm sorry!

276
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:11,670
Did you just receive mail that said, "Thank you?"

277
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:14,170
Yes, I did.

278
00:16:14,170 --> 00:16:16,955
Then, are you the one who made that deduction?

279
00:16:18,170 --> 00:16:20,959
No, I don't know anything about this mail.

280
00:16:20,959 --> 00:16:24,963
What? But, the mail was sent from your cell phone, right?

281
00:16:25,170 --> 00:16:26,470
Yes.

282
00:16:26,470 --> 00:16:30,370
It could be the person who picked up my cell phone a while ago.

283
00:16:30,370 --> 00:16:32,370
A man who was wearing a black cap

284
00:16:32,370 --> 00:16:35,670
and had a burn scar on his right cheek.

285
00:16:35,670 --> 00:16:36,975
What?

286
00:16:36,975 --> 00:16:38,970
Where is that man?

287
00:16:38,970 --> 00:16:40,070
Yes.

288
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:42,470
He went over to the escalator that started moving.

289
00:16:42,470 --> 00:16:44,670
I think he went downstairs?

290
00:16:45,870 --> 00:16:46,985
Conan?

291
00:16:54,070 --> 00:16:56,770
What's up? What's the rush?

292
00:16:56,770 --> 00:16:58,997
Jodie.

293
00:16:58,997 --> 00:17:03,870
Don't tell me you're looking for the same person I am?

294
00:17:03,870 --> 00:17:05,570
No.

295
00:17:05,570 --> 00:17:07,770
Just as the message in question said,

296
00:17:07,770 --> 00:17:11,009
it seems that this place is definitely dangerous.

297
00:17:12,070 --> 00:17:14,070
Message in question?

298
00:17:14,070 --> 00:17:17,370
The message that Shu gave me!

299
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:19,770
You met him? Mr. Akai?

300
00:17:19,770 --> 00:17:23,770
No, when I left my seat for a while at the cafe in the basement,

301
00:17:23,770 --> 00:17:27,025
he secretly wrote it in the back of the coaster!

302
00:17:28,070 --> 00:17:31,870
And, why is it dangerous here?

303
00:17:31,870 --> 00:17:34,270
The bomb scare incident's been solved, right?

304
00:17:34,270 --> 00:17:36,070
Because I saw it.

305
00:17:36,070 --> 00:17:38,770
A sniper-like person was seen from a window of the hotel opposite

306
00:17:38,770 --> 00:17:41,039
this department store.

307
00:17:41,039 --> 00:17:45,370
And parked right below, is a black Porsche 356A.

308
00:17:45,370 --> 00:17:46,370
Gin!

309
00:17:46,370 --> 00:17:49,670
Don't tell me, that he found out that Shu is alive

310
00:17:49,670 --> 00:17:51,370
and is planning to shoot him?

311
00:17:52,570 --> 00:17:53,870
Shu!

312
00:17:53,870 --> 00:17:55,053
Where are you, Shu?

313
00:18:01,470 --> 00:18:03,770
There he is. It's Shu!

314
00:18:03,770 --> 00:18:05,070
No, Shu!

315
00:18:05,070 --> 00:18:06,770
Don't go out!

316
00:18:06,770 --> 00:18:08,670
They're coming after you!

317
00:18:08,670 --> 00:18:10,070
Shu!

318
00:18:13,071 --> 00:18:16,270
I'm sorry. Are you all right?

319
00:18:16,270 --> 00:18:19,770
The rate of taking the blame would be fifty-fifty.

320
00:18:19,770 --> 00:18:21,570
You weren't careful and attentive enough,

321
00:18:21,570 --> 00:18:23,570
you're to be blame too.

322
00:18:23,570 --> 00:18:25,770
Yes.

323
00:18:25,770 --> 00:18:27,870
You looked to have been looking for someone?

324
00:18:27,870 --> 00:18:28,870
Shu!

325
00:18:28,870 --> 00:18:31,089
Where are you, Shu?

326
00:18:33,270 --> 00:18:35,970
There he is! I found him!

327
00:18:35,970 --> 00:18:38,170
I found the phantom!

328
00:18:38,170 --> 00:18:40,770
On the left edge of the main entrance.

329
00:18:40,770 --> 00:18:43,370
Right to the side of your car!

330
00:18:43,370 --> 00:18:46,070
Hurry up and check it out if you're going to, Gin!

331
00:18:46,070 --> 00:18:48,170
Because my finger that's on the trigger

332
00:18:48,170 --> 00:18:50,170
is impatiently waiting and twitching

333
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:52,870
and may go off any minute!

334
00:18:54,470 --> 00:18:56,470
Akai Shuichi.

335
00:19:02,570 --> 00:19:04,070
Vermouth.

336
00:19:07,770 --> 00:19:11,129
Did you get approval from that person?

337
00:19:11,370 --> 00:19:14,670
Yes, boss is very discreet and careful.

338
00:19:14,670 --> 00:19:18,170
Maybe too careful that the timing goes off.

339
00:19:18,170 --> 00:19:19,770
What the heck are you doing?

340
00:19:19,770 --> 00:19:22,570
Can I kill him? Or not?

341
00:19:22,570 --> 00:19:23,870
Which is it going to be?

342
00:19:25,670 --> 00:19:27,470
What the...

343
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:28,770
He looked...

344
00:19:28,770 --> 00:19:29,970
That guy!

345
00:19:29,970 --> 00:19:31,970
He looked this way!

346
00:19:31,970 --> 00:19:33,670
He looked at me and laughed!

347
00:19:33,670 --> 00:19:35,153
Do I kill him or not?

348
00:19:35,153 --> 00:19:37,155
What do I do?

349
00:19:37,155 --> 00:19:39,970
Gin, it's strange, right?

350
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:44,370
The customers are rushing back into the department store.

351
00:19:44,370 --> 00:19:46,870
Where is he? Where'd he go?

352
00:19:46,870 --> 00:19:49,167
The shoppers are suddenly rushing along.

353
00:19:49,167 --> 00:19:50,570
It's hard to lock him on.

354
00:19:50,570 --> 00:19:53,670
Hey, doesn't it look bad?

355
00:19:53,670 --> 00:19:55,173
She's got a rifle.

356
00:19:55,370 --> 00:19:58,070
Maybe their shooting a film or something?

357
00:19:59,670 --> 00:20:02,470
-Let's go. -What?

358
00:20:02,470 --> 00:20:04,170
Tell Korn too.

359
00:20:04,170 --> 00:20:07,185
Hey, just what's going on? Gin...

360
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:10,670
Priority on his own discretion again.

361
00:20:10,670 --> 00:20:13,191
Revolting like always.

362
00:20:13,191 --> 00:20:16,270
What? Who are you talking about?

363
00:20:16,270 --> 00:20:18,570
Like you said,

364
00:20:18,570 --> 00:20:22,370
you wish they leave detectives

365
00:20:22,370 --> 00:20:25,870
like Sherlock Holmes locked up in novels only.

366
00:21:47,285 --> 00:21:49,870
Hey, hurry up and give me the gift certificate!

367
00:21:49,870 --> 00:21:52,970
You're giving us 10,000 yen worth, aren't you?

368
00:21:52,970 --> 00:21:54,970
Just what're you talking about?

369
00:21:54,970 --> 00:21:57,070
A boy wearing glasses went around shouting

370
00:21:57,070 --> 00:21:59,770
that as an apology of the bomb scare,

371
00:21:59,770 --> 00:22:03,070
you're giving away gift certificate to all the customers who came!

372
00:22:03,770 --> 00:22:06,770
I haven't heard anything sort of thing.

373
00:22:06,770 --> 00:22:09,070
Hey, come on, man!

374
00:22:09,070 --> 00:22:11,309
I came all the way back here.

375
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:14,670
I see, gift certificates, right?

376
00:22:14,670 --> 00:22:17,315
I wouldn't say that it was too bright.

377
00:22:17,315 --> 00:22:19,070
But, I guess it couldn't be helped

378
00:22:19,070 --> 00:22:21,319
if you wanted to evacuate the customers from here, right?

379
00:22:21,319 --> 00:22:23,321
Subaru?

380
00:22:23,321 --> 00:22:25,970
I had some business to take care of at the Teito Bank

381
00:22:25,970 --> 00:22:27,325
near this department store.

382
00:22:27,325 --> 00:22:30,170
So, I did what I had to do and came out saw you all,

383
00:22:30,170 --> 00:22:33,770
and ran after you thinking to call you,

384
00:22:33,770 --> 00:22:36,070
and got messed up in the incident.

385
00:22:36,070 --> 00:22:38,170
Who is this guy?

386
00:22:38,170 --> 00:22:41,339
I hear that his apartment was burnt down.

387
00:22:41,339 --> 00:22:43,670
He lives at Shinichi's house for the time being,

388
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:46,270
and his name is Mr. Subaru Okiya, a university student.

389
00:22:46,270 --> 00:22:47,670
I see...

390
00:22:47,670 --> 00:22:49,670
But, what was that about?

391
00:22:49,670 --> 00:22:53,351
Conan evacuating the customers a while ago.

392
00:22:55,353 --> 00:22:57,870
It's not worth hearing about.

393
00:22:57,870 --> 00:22:59,670
It's a worthless story

394
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:02,270
about a bunch of stupid wolves letting the prey

395
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:04,370
that they hunted down get away.

396
00:23:04,370 --> 00:23:09,670
But, you live quite a distance away from Teito Bank, don't you?

397
00:23:09,670 --> 00:23:12,170
Why would you have a saving account in a place like that?

398
00:23:12,170 --> 00:23:13,371
No.

399
00:23:13,371 --> 00:23:16,770
I had other things to do at that bank.

400
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:18,370
Other things to do?

401
00:23:18,370 --> 00:23:22,970
Remember the robbery at that bank some time ago?

402
00:23:22,970 --> 00:23:25,383
In the news that was aired to look back on that case,

403
00:23:25,383 --> 00:23:27,370
I saw my acquaintance.

404
00:23:27,370 --> 00:23:32,370
I went there thinking that maybe he was using that bank.

405
00:23:32,370 --> 00:23:35,670
If he's using that bank, he should be living in this vicinity.

406
00:23:35,670 --> 00:23:38,770
I was hoping to get lucky and run into him.

407
00:23:38,770 --> 00:23:42,270
So, you didn't get to see him?

408
00:23:42,270 --> 00:23:45,970
Well, I coincidentally saw him on that floor.

409
00:23:45,970 --> 00:23:48,570
But, unfortunately, it seemed to be someone else,

410
00:23:48,570 --> 00:23:50,370
so I didn't call out to him.

411
00:23:52,470 --> 00:23:55,970
His face is one that I've known for a long time,

412
00:23:55,970 --> 00:23:58,570
so I'd never mistaken him for someone else.

